e"},"92":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-5","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","type":"heading","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"url":"/docs/glossary/modality#heading-4","content":"Where It Appears"},"93":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-6","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","type":"heading","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"url":"/docs/glossary/modality#heading-5","content":"Common Confusions"},"94":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-7","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","type":"heading","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"url":"/docs/glossary/modality#heading-6","content":"Related Concepts And Modules"},"95":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-8","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","type":"heading","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"url":"/docs/glossary/modality#heading-7","content":"Tags"},"96":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-9","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","type":"heading","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"url":"/docs/glossary/modality#heading-8","content":"References"},"97":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-10","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality#Modality","content":"The kind of input or output data a model is built to handle, such as text, images, audio, or video.\n\nModality\nThe kind of input or output data a model is built to handle, such as text, images, audio, or video.\nModality names the data channel—text tokens, pixels, or spectrograms—not the architecture or trained checkpoint powering a model.\nWhat It Is\nA modality is a data type the model consumes or produces. Unimodal models specialize in one channel; multimodal models align two or more, such as image patches with text tokens. Modality sits above representation: it names what is encoded, not the internal vector format.\nWhy It Matters\nModality tells you which encoders, tokenizers, and fusion modules to expect before you open a family page. It also separates \"handles images\" from \"is a diffusion architecture\" or \"is a foundation model.\"\nSimple Example\nA speech-to-text system pairs an audio waveform modality with a text output modality. A text-only LLM has a single text modality end to end even when users paste images in a chat UI—the product may be multimodal while the core model is not.\nWhere It Appears\nModality appears in model cards, dataset documentation, and multimodal family overviews. The model glossary page links here when describing what a checkpoint accepts.\nCommon Confusions\nModality is not architecture: a transformer can be text-only or multimodal depending on inputs. Modality is also not representation—a modality is the raw channel, while representation is the learned internal form after encoding.\nRelated Concepts And Modules\nTags\nReferences\nReader Shortcut\nList the input and output data types first; that list is the modality story before you compare parameters or benchmarks."},"98":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-11","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality","content":"data modality"},"99":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-12","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality","content":"input modality"},"100":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-13","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality","content":"multimodal input"},"101":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-14","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality","content":"taxonomy"},"102":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-15","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality","content":"glossary taxonomy"},"103":{"id":"/docs/glossary/modality-16","page_id":"/docs/glossary/modality","tags":["taxonomy","foundations"],"type":"text","url":"/docs/glossary/modality","content":"atlas t